name: Peaches
directions: Unmarked black doors by the entrance
comment: you should be a customer

name: Bedford Hall
comment: You need to be a customer.

name: Berg'n
directions: Single room family restroom near the other bathrooms.

name: Berg'n
directions: When entering, walk to the mirrors straight ahead (left of the bar) and turn left.  Bathrooms will be on your left before the staircase.
comment: There are gendered bathrooms and a gender neutral bathroom between them.

name: Doris
directions: There is a first floor bathroom (accessible) and then there are three bathrooms downstairs. All are gender neutral, all private single stalls with functioning locks.
comment: It's a bar, so do you, though only open 5pm-2am, but no one will bother you about using the bathroom! Also, staff is nice. Alert them if you need assistance or do not feel safe.

name: Franklin Park
directions: By the skee ball machine!
comment: It's a fun bar, too!

name: Bombay Heights
directions: Back of the restaurant
comment: You must be a paying customer

name: C'mon Everybody
directions: One restroom on the left past the bar, another in the music room to the right of the stage

name: The Way Station
directions: One large single (Tardis) which is accessible, second restroom labelled All Gender Lavatory
comment: It is a bar. But pretty safe.

name: Taqueria de los Muertos
comment: Buy something at counter first

name: Speedy Romeo
directions: Back right corner
comment: Two gender neutral single stall bathrooms

name: Brooklyn Kolache
directions: At the end of the tables to the far right.
comment: Really sweet staff, you can just ask or walk right in.

name: Brooklyn Museum
directions: this is on the left when you enter the building in the lobby area.
comment: no need to pay entry into the museum.

name: Brooklyn Museum
directions: in the lobby to the left when you enter the building.
comment: no need to pay entry into museum. there are two handicap accessible single stall bathrooms that are also labeled as gender neutral. when i was last there (sept 2019) the museum also had a sign up in the restroom area saying people are allowed to use any bathroom that fits their gender identity.

name: Project Parlor
directions: all one floor, towards the back of the bar
comment: friendly dive bar, lots of queer/trans clientele

name: Soda
directions: Straight in to the end of the bar, on the right (next to kitchen).
comment: It's a bar, so act like you're drinking.

name: Wendy's
directions: Right by the entrance on your right
comment: I just walked in and used it, no purchase required, but they'd probably appreciate if you bought something small if you can.

name: Rebecca's
directions: Walk to the back, you'll see it on the left
comment:
Open 6pm to 4am
Just go in and use the bathroom, no purchase required!

name: SUNY Downstate Basic Sciences Building- 6th floor
directions: by the hallway that connects the basic sciences building and the education building
comment: you have to be a student/staff/visitor to the school to access the bathroom

name: Thai 101
comment: Great food too.

name: Tea Lounge
comment: Monday-Thursday 7am-1am  :  Friday 7am-2am  :  Saturday 8am-2am  :  Sunday 8am-1am

name: Ramen Takumi
street: northeast corner of Washington Square Park
directions: All the way back and to the left.
comment: You have to be a customer. Accessible (largish room, metal bars behind & to left side of toilet) but pathway back may be a little narrow for a wheelchair.

name: Sweetwater Coffee & Tea
comment: Customers only so buy a delicious cookie

name: Parkside
directions: On the left just past the bar

name: Alchemy
directions: Towards the back to the left

name: Rose Water
directions: Straight back from the entrance
comment: crowded on weekends

name: Brooklyn Public Library - Bushwick location
directions: go to the customer service desk in the front. The key to the restroom is kept in a plastic bin on the edge of desk. If the bin is empty, wait for the key to come back before taking the elevator to the basement or the stairs.

name: Berlyn
directions: To the right, across from the bar.

name: Tutu's
directions: Straight to the back, past the bar and the tables in the hallway to the back room. It'll be to your right.

name: Center for Fiction
directions: By the café in back, no need to buy anything!

name: Syndicated
directions: In the back, marked WC. A row of single rooms with a common trough sink outside
comment: beautiful & inexpensive movie theatre where they also serve food. Recommended! probably won't notice during busy times if you walk past looking for a friend

name: Brooklyn Public Library
directions: On the main floor near the seating area, next to the staircase

name: Blick Art Materials
directions: Bottom floor, accessible through elevator or stairs.
comment: Just ask for restroom.

name: Pine Box Rock Shop

name: Lantern Hall
comment: Restrooms are single stalls, explicitly marked as "all-gender" restrooms

name: Wild East Brewing Co.

name: The Graham

name: Culture
directions: Along the left wall towards the back

name: Champs diner
directions: There are two, gender-neutral, single-stall restrooms at the back of the restaurant on the right.
comment: The staff are very accepting.

name: Champ's Diner
directions: Through the restaurant at the back wall.

name: Mil Mundos Books
comment: SAFE SPACE 💖

name: Alamo draft house
directions: In lobby of the movie theater. Near escalator.

name: Heavy Woods
directions: Straight back and to the left, across from the where plates are placed for waitstaff

name: Alamo Drafthouse

name: Good Morning Brooklyn

name: Lavender Lake

name: Bridge and Tunnel Brewery

name: Chipotle
directions: You'll need to ask at the register for the code for the bathroom. Everyone is really nice and accepting. I work there an am trans 😊

name: Taco Chulo
directions: In the back on the right

name: M Shanghai Bistro
directions: In the back near the exit to the patio to the right

name: The Brick Theater
directions: to the right, past the box office counter

name: 61 Local
directions: back of space. two restrooms. both single occupancy and neutral.

name: Panera bread
directions: Towards the back
comment: You may need to ask the cashier for a key, but it seems that that is not in practice. There is urinal and a toilet.

name: decoursey's sidecar bar and grille

name: Bia

name: Lowlands bar/cafe
comment: Just ask to use the bathroom- staff is super friendly - cafe by day, bar by night. Single stall upstairs & downstairs

name: Lowlands bar/cafe
comment: Just ask to use the bathroom- staff is super friendly - cafe by day, bar by night. Single stall upstairs & downstairs

name: Hinterlands Bar

name: Lions Milk

name: Cafe Madeline
comment: They won't kick up a fuss if you don't buy anything but it would probably be helpful to try to buy something

name: Chipotle
directions: On the lefthand side as you enter
comment: Ask the cashier for the lock code

name: Crif Dogs

name: Crif Dogs

name: Topos bookstore

name: Topos bookstore

comment: Nice bookstore w coffee and nice staff

name: Starbucks

name: Sea witch
directions: Easy to locate, next to the bar area across from the kitchen

name: Chai Thai Kitchen
directions: Small restaurant. Walk past bar toward kitchen and bathroom will be on right hand side. 1 bathroom in the joint.

name: Chai Thai Kitchen
directions: Small restaurant. Walk past bar toward kitchen and bathroom will be on right hand side. 1 bathroom in the joint.
comment: You'll probably need to buy something but the food is good and the bathroom is clean.

name: Other Half Brewing Co.
comment: There’s 4/5 stalls and each one is gender inclusive. Common area hand washing

name: Rough Trade

name: Shake Shack
directions: In the back, to the right

name: Starbucks
directions: This Starbucks is near Brooklyn College and the Flatbush Junction.  There is one genderfree, single-occupancy bathroom with a locking door.  Walk in and go straight past the counter, the bathroom will be on the left.  The door is usually open for anyone to use the bathroom.
comment: As of spring 2009, regular hours are Mon-Fri 6am-10pm, and Sat-Sun 7:30am-10pm.  During college breaks, they often close early.  Call them at 718-338-2489 to check hours.

name: Bard High School Early College
directions: A single stall gender neutral bathroom available on each floor . On the 4th floor there are currently 2 multi-stall gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: All students and teachers allowed as well as most visitors!

name: Brooklyn College Library Cafe
directions: There are 3 gender-neutral, single-stall bathrooms in the Library Cafe near Whitehead Hall.  One of the bathrooms is accessible.
comment: The Library Cafe is open 24 hours a day except certain holidays.  You must show a student or staff ID to enter the Brooklyn College campus.

name: Milk and Honey Cafe
directions: Ground floor, back of cafe
